                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="41517" author="jeremyg484" created="Tue, 9 Dec 2008 05:24:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Now ensuring the updated component state gets stored across the redirect for a recursive transition.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="43417" author="nkaza" created="Mon, 30 Mar 2009 23:48:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since FlowViewHandler.restoreFlowView checks if ViewRoot.viewId equals resourcePath if you declare the view with no sufix:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;view-state view=&quot;myView&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;then this fix will not be applied, right? I guess there should be a note on the documentation that views should be declared with full sufix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;view-state view=&quot;myView.xhtml&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="43418" author="jeremyg484" created="Tue, 31 Mar 2009 00:05:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That is incorrect...the JSF UIViewRoot&apos;s viewId should already be set to the full path of the resource.  It is a slightly different concept from the Web Flow view id.  We handle the translation between the two within the FlowViewHandler.  It should be fine to leave off the file suffix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="43428" author="nkaza" created="Tue, 31 Mar 2009 03:02:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry if I&apos;m mistaken, I think the translation you are mentioning happens in FlowViewHandler.resolveResourcePath( ) right? From what I see, if it is an absolute path, there is no suffix appended. In fact, the viewId is returned as is.&lt;br/&gt;
		if (viewId.startsWith(&quot;/&quot;)) &lt;/p&gt;
{
			return viewId;
		}
&lt;p&gt; else {&lt;br/&gt;
With my setup the viewId does not include the suffix. The suffix is actually added by the default ViewHandler, taking into account my javax.faces.DEFAULT_SUFFIX parameter in web.xml. That is because I have mapped the dispatcher-servlet with a suffix mapping (*.htm). Therefore, UIViewRoot has a viewId with the suffix but resourcePath does not. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="43452" author="nkaza" created="Wed, 1 Apr 2009 01:39:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, as far as I can see, the extension is added by the framework (FlowModelFlowBuilder) only if the view=&quot;&quot; attribute is omitted on the view-state declaration. It isn&apos;t added by the translation mentioned above. So, unless the view attribute is omitted, a suffix should always be added. I see the reference manual includes a suffix anywhere a view=&quot;&quot; attribute is used, so I guess no changes are required.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
